trend_summary: The territory evolves from dispersed housing amid large forest blocks to a noticeably fuller suburban mosaic. New subdivisions spread west-central and southeast, industrial roofs enlarge along the central highway, and several farmland parcels shrink. Tree cover declines slightly but pockets of reforestation appear north. Overall change indicates steady, moderate suburban growth without high-rise intensification.
notable_changes: Multiple new curvilinear housing tracts fill previously wooded plots in the west-central section.
Expansion of white-roof warehouse/industrial complex along the north-south highway corridor.
Gradual reduction of open farmland in eastern pockets, converted to mixed residential use.
Minor infill and widening of arterial roads improving connectivity between clusters.
Some small northern parcels show tree regrowth where cleared land existed earlier.
